HEADWORD: Peroration
<hw>Per`o*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>peroratio</ets>, fr. <ets>perorate</ets>, <ets>peroratum</ets>, to
speak from beginning to end; <ets>per</ets> + <ets>orate</ets> to speak.
See <er>Per-</er>, and <er>Oration</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld>
<def>The concluding part of an oration; especially, a final summing up
and enforcement of an argument.</def> <rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

